quran[62]{c,v,t}:
  37,83,One of his followers in iman was Ibrahim
  37,84,when he came to his Lord with an unblemished heart
  37,85,"and said to his father and his people, ´What are you worshipping"
  37,86,Is it falsehood — gods besides Allah — that you desire
  37,87,So what are your thoughts about the Lord of all the worlds?´
  37,88,He took a look at the stars
  37,89,"and said, ´I am sick.´"
  37,90,So they turned their backs on him
  37,91,"He turned surreptitiously to their gods and said, ´Do you not eat"
  37,92,What is the matter with you that you do not speak?´
  37,93,"He turned on them, striking out with his right hand"
  37,94,They came rushing back to him
  37,95,"He said, ´Do you worship something you have carved"
  37,96,when Allah created both you and what you do?´
  37,97,"They said, ´Build a pyre for him and fling him into the blaze!´"
  37,98,They tried to outwit him but We made them the lowest
  37,99,"He said, ´I am going towards my Lord; He will be my guide"
  37,100,"My Lord, bestow on me a right-acting child!´"
  37,101,And We gave him the good news of a forbearing boy
  37,102,"When he was of an age to work with him, he said, ´My son, I saw in a dream that I must sacrifice you. What do you think about this?´ He said, ´Do as you are ordered, father. Allah willing, you will find me resolute.´"
  37,103,Then when they had both submitted and he had lain him face down on the ground
  37,104,"We called out to him, ´Ibrahim"
  37,105,you have discharged your vision.´ That is how We recompense good-doers
  37,106,This was indeed a most manifest trial
  37,107,We ransomed him with a mighty sacrifice
  37,108,and left the later people saying of him
  37,109,´Peace be upon Ibrahim.´
  37,110,That is how We recompense good-doers
  37,111,He truly was one of Our mumin slaves
  37,112,"We gave him the good news of Ishaq, a Prophet, one of the righteous"
  37,113,We showered blessings upon him and upon Ishaq. Among their descendants are good-doers and also people who clearly wrong themselves
  37,114,We showed great kindness to Musa and Harun
  37,115,We rescued them and their people from their terrible plight
  37,116,We supported them and so they were the victors
  37,117,We gave them the clarifying Book
  37,118,and guided them on the Straight Path
  37,119,and left the later people saying of them
  37,120,´Peace be upon Musa and Harun!´
  37,121,That is how We recompense good-doers
  37,122,They truly were among Our slaves who are muminun
  37,123,Ilyas was one of the Messengers
  37,124,"When he said to his people, ´Will you not have taqwa"
  37,125,Do you call on Baal and abandon the Best of Creators
  37,126,"Allah is your Lord and Lord of your forefathers, the previous peoples,´"
  37,127,they denied him and so they will be among those arraigned —
  37,128,except for Allah´s chosen slaves
  37,129,We left the later people saying of him
  37,130,´Peace be upon the family of Yasin!´
  37,131,That is how We recompense good-doers
  37,132,He truly was one of Our slaves who are muminun
  37,133,And Lut was one of the Messengers
  37,134,When We rescued him and all his family —
  37,135,except an old woman among those who stayed behind
  37,136,Then We utterly destroyed the rest
  37,137,And you pass by them in the daytime and at night
  37,138,So will you not use your intellect
  37,139,Yunus too was one of the Messengers
  37,140,When he ran away to the fully laden ship
  37,141,and cast lots and lost
  37,142,Then the fish devoured him and he was to blame
  37,143,Had it not been that he was a man who glorified Allah
  37,144,he would have remained inside its belly until the Day they are raised again